### Error: "Failed to refresh access token" OR Missing OAuth Token

**What user sees**:
- Tools were working, now they fail with empty results or errors
- OR first-time setup and OAuth hasn't been completed yet

**Common error messages:**
```
Error: invalid_grant: Token has been expired or revoked
No valid existing credentials found
```

**What happened**:
- OAuth token expired, was revoked, or was deleted
- OR first-time setup (no token exists yet)

**How gworkspace-mcp handles this:**

✅ **Automatic OAuth re-authentication** - The server handles this gracefully!

**What happens when token is missing:**
1. ✅ **Server stays green** (doesn't validate token at startup)
2. ✅ **First tool invocation triggers OAuth automatically**
3. ✅ **Browser opens for authentication** (no manual steps needed)
4. ✅ **User accepts permissions**
5. ✅ **Token saved, tool execution continues**

**Log example (what you'll see in logs):**
```
[2025-10-29 10:04:29] No valid existing credentials found. Initiating new authentication flow.
[2025-10-29 10:04:29] Initiating new OAuth flow for scopes: ['https://www.googleapis.com/auth/drive.readonly']
[2025-10-29 10:04:29] Opening browser for authentication...
[2025-10-29 10:04:38] Successfully exchanged authorization code for credentials
[2025-10-29 10:04:38] New credentials saved to /Users/username/.gworkspace_mcp/oauth_token.pickle
```

**No manual fix needed!** Just:
1. **Invoke any tool** (e.g., "Search my Drive for files")
2. **Browser opens automatically** - wait for it (takes 1-2 seconds)
3. **Select your @shopify.com account**
4. **Check "Select all"** on the permissions screen
5. **Click "Continue"** to grant permissions
6. **Done!** Token is saved, tool executes

**If you want to force re-authentication manually:**

```bash
# Delete the token
rm ~/.gworkspace_mcp/oauth_token.pickle

# No need to toggle server - just use a tool and OAuth will trigger
```

**Important notes:**
- ✅ Server doesn't need restart after token deletion
- ✅ No need to toggle OFF/ON
- ✅ OAuth triggers automatically on next tool use
- ⚠️ Make sure to select your **@shopify.com** account (not personal Gmail)

